# Kubernetes TLS Certificate Error — Resolution Guide

## ❗ Error Summary
When applying a Kubernetes manifest:

```bash
kubectl apply -f nginx-deploy.yaml
You may encounter:

Code
tls: failed to verify certificate: x509: certificate signed by unknown authority
This happens when kubectl cannot validate the Kubernetes API server certificate.

🎯 Root Cause
kubectl is not using the correct kubeconfig file.

Common reasons:

Missing $HOME/.kube/config

Running as root without exporting the correct config

admin.conf not copied to the user’s kube directory

Incorrect or corrupted kubeconfig

✅ Resolution Steps
1. Export the correct kubeconfig
bash
export KUBECONFIG=/etc/kubernetes/admin.conf
2. Verify access
bash
kubectl get nodes
3. Make the fix persistent
bash
echo "export KUBECONFIG=/etc/kubernetes/admin.conf" >> ~/.bashrc
source ~/.bashrc
4. (Optional) Copy kubeconfig to default location
bash
mkdir -p $HOME/.kube
cp /etc/kubernetes/admin.conf $HOME/.kube/config
chown $(id -u):$(id -g) $HOME/.kube/config
5. Re-run your manifest
bash
kubectl apply -f nginx-deploy.yaml
✔️ Result
kubectl can now authenticate properly and communicate with the Kubernetes API server without TLS validation errors.
